#Text=The Milwaukee Bucks ( 2 - 3 ) defeated the Philadelphia 76ers ( 0 - 4 ) by a score of 91 - 87 on Wednesday at the BMO Harris Bradley Center in Milwaukee Despite being the expected favorite coming in , the Bucks were n't able to get any sort of lead through the first three quarters , as time and again , the Sixers held strong .

#Text=The Sixers eventually had an 85 - 82 lead with two and half minutes left in regulation , but the Bucks went on to outscore them 9 - 2 in the final two minutes to pull out the four - point victory in front of their home crowd .
#Text=The Bucks were outrebounded 51 - 37 in this one , but forced the Sixers into 19 turnovers , which ended up making the difference .
#Text=Struggling to get momentum this year , Khris Middleton finally turned things around Wednesday .

#Text=Although he did n't have the best shooting percentage , he still led the team with 21 points ( 7 - 20 FG , 3 - 7 3Pt , 4 - 4 FT ) , including a clutch three - pointer to put the Bucks up four points with less than 50 seconds in the game .
#Text=Middleton was continually called upon for late - game heroics during the 2014 - 15 season , so Milwaukee was very happy to see the swingman return to form again Wednesday .
#Text=Greg Monroe also was able to have success in this one , showing the young bigs of the Sixers his experience .
#Text=Monroe finished with 18 points ( 7 - 14 FG , 4 - 5 FT ) , eight rebounds , and three steals over 36 minutes .
#Text=He 's now combined for an impressive 41 points and 21 rebounds over his last two outings .
#Text=Giannis Antetokounmpo chipped in with an efficient 17 points ( 7 - 11 FG , 1 - 1 3Pt , 2 - 3 FT ) and five rebounds of his own .
#Text=Despite struggling to limit Monroe defensively , rookie Jahlil Okafor and second - year pro Nerlens Noel performed admirably on the offensive side of the ball .
#Text=Okafor recorded 21 points ( 9 - 13 FG , 3 - 3 FT ) , six rebounds , and two blocked shots , while Noel finished with 17 points ( 8 - 16 FG , 1 - 2 FT ) , 12 rebounds , and one blocked shot .
#Text=Noel has now notched three double - doubles over the first four games of the season , pushing his season averages to 12 points and 10 rebounds .
#Text=Nik Stauskas was the only other Sixer in double figures with 14 points , but went a dreadful 3 - of - 14 from behind the three - point line .
#Text=The Sixers will next head to Cleveland to play the Cavaliers on Friday , while the Bucks will be on the road against the New York Knicks on Friday .
